ydalton.html |archivedate=5 May 2008|accessdate=26 February 2012}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Derwent Valley Heritage Way]] || {{convert|55|mi|km|0|disp=table|sortable=on}} || [[Derbyshire]] || [[Ladybower Reservoir]], north of [[Bamford]] || [[Shardlow]] || Runs around the [[Derbyshire Dales]] through [[Chatsworth, Derbyshire]] and the [[Derwent Valley Mills]] [[World Heritage Site]].\n|-\n|[[Fen Rivers Way]] || {{convert|50|mi|km|0|disp=table|sortable=on}} || Eastern England || [[Cambridge]] || [[King's Lynn]], [[Norfolk]] || Runs alongside the [[River Cam]] and on to the [[River Great Ouse]].\n|-\n|[[Geopark Way]] || {{convert|109|mi|km|0|disp=table|sortable=on}} || [[West Midlands (region)|West Midlands]] and South West England || [[Bridgnorth Castle]] || [[Gloucester Cathedral]] || Links a series of geologically and historically important sites.<ref name=GeoparkWay>{{cite web | title = Geopark Way | publisher = LDWA | url = http://www.ldwa.org.uk/ldp/members/show_path.php?path_id=8201  | accessdate = 19 August 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Gloucestershire Way]] || {{convert|100|mi|km|0|disp=table|sortable=on}} || [[Gloucestershire]] || [[Tutshill]] || [[Tewkesbury]] || Routes through the [[Forest of Dean]], [[Cotswolds]] and the [[Severn Plain]].\n|-\n|[[Gritstone Trail]] || {{convert|35|mi|km|0|disp=table|sortable=on}} || [[Cheshire East]] and [[Staffordshire]] || [[Disley railway station]], [[Disley]] || [[Mow Cop]], [[Kidsgrove]] || Mostly through the western section of the [[Peak District]] National Park.\n|-\n|[[Heart of England Way]] || {{convert|100|mi|km|0|disp=table|sortable=on}} || [[English Midlands|Midlands]] || [[Milford, Staffordshire|Milford]], Staffordshire || [[Bourton-on-the-Water]], Gloucestershire || Links the [[Cannock Chase|Cannock Chase Area of Outstanding Natural Beauty]] with the [[Cotswolds#Area of Outstanding Natural Beauty|Cotswolds Area of Outstanding Natural Beauty]]; officially recognised by the four councils it passes through.<ref>{{cite web|url=https