ire || N/A || N/A || Annual circular route around former [[RAF]] Pathfinder airfields in [[Cambridgeshire]], held on the Saturday closest to Midsummers Day.\n|-\n|[[Peak District Boundary Walk]] || {{convert|190|mi|km|0|disp=table|sortable=on}} || Derbyshire, Cheshire, Yorkshire, Staffordshire || [[Buxton]] Market Place || [[Buxton]] Market Place || A circular walking trail, broadly following the boundary of the [[Peak District]] national park. The route was developed by the Friends of the Peak District (a branch of the [[Campaign to Protect Rural England]]).\n|-\n|[[Robin Hood Way]] || {{convert|104|mi|km|0|disp=table|sortable=on}} || The Midlands || [[Nottingham Castle]] || [[Edwinstowe]], [[Sherwood Forest]] || Commemorates the [[folklore]] of [[Robin Hood]].\n|-\n|[[Sabrina Way]] || {{convert|203|mi|km|0|disp=table|sortable=on}} || The Midlands and Central England || [[Hartington, Derbyshire|Hartington]], Derbyshire || [[Great Barrington, Gloucestershire|Great Barrington]], Gloucestershire|| [[Bridleway]] providing a link between the Ridgeway and the [[Pennine Bridleway]].\n|-\n|[[Saffron Trail]] || {{convert|70|mi|km|0|disp=table|sortable=on}} || Essex || [[Southend on Sea]] || [[Saffron Walden]] || Traverses the county from the south-east to the north-west.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.essexwalks.com/walks/saffron_trail.html#page=page-1|title=Saffron Trail|last=|first=|date=|website=www.essexwalks.com|publisher=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ldwa.org.uk/ldp/members/show_path.php?path_name=Saffron+Trail|title=LDWA Saffron Trail|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher= Long Distance Walker's Association|access-date=}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Sandlings Walk]] || {{convert|60|mi|km|0|disp=table|sortable=on}} || [[Suffolk]] || [[Ipswich]] || [[Southwold]] || Has eleven sculptures along the route and passes through the [[Suffolk Coast and Heaths]] [[Area of Outstanding Natural Beauty]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ldwa.org.uk/ldp/members/show_path.php?